(x,y) = (x_1, y_1)
(x,y) = (x_2, y_2)
(x_3,y_3)
(x_4,y_4)
(x_2 - x_1) y + (y_1 - y_2) x = - x_1 y_2 + x_2 y_1
(x_4 - x_3) y + (y_3 - y_4) x = - x_3 y_4 + x_4 y_3
y=mx+c
y_1=mx_1+c
y_2=mx_2+c
(y-y_1)=m(x-x_1)
(y_2-y)=m(x_2-x)
m
m=\frac{y-y_1}{x-x_1}=\frac{y_2-y}{x_2-x}
x_2y-x_2y_1-xy+xy_1=xy_2-xy-x_1y_2+x_1y
